                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="appalachianmountains_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a range of mountains in eastern North America. It runs 1 800 miles/2 900 kilometres from Newfoundland in Canada to central Alabama in the US. This includes the region of <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/appalachia" title="Appalachia definition"><span class="ndv">Appalachia</span></a> and the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-allegheny-mountains#the_allegheny_mountains_topg_1" title="Allegheny Mountains definition"><span class="ndv">Allegheny Mountains</span></a>, the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-great-smoky-mountains#the_great_smoky_mountains_topg_1" title="Great Smoky Mountains definition"><span class="ndv">Great Smoky Mountains</span></a> and the Blue Ridge Mountains. The Appalachian National Scenic Trail is a long-distance path with signs for <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/hiker#hiker_topg_1" title="hikers definition"><span class="ndv">hikers</span></a> <span class="gloss" hclass="gloss" htag="span">(= people walking for pleasure)</span>.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
